HB 892 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Hilferty
Abstract: Creates the West End Economic Development District in the parishes of
Jefferson and Orleans.
Proposed law creates the West End Economic Development District as a political
subdivision in the parishes of Jefferson and Orleans to promote and encourage economic and
commercial development and tourism opportunities. Provides for district boundaries.
Proposed law provides that the district is governed by a five-member board of
commissioners composed as follows:
(1) Two members appointed by the member of the governing authority of Jefferson
Parish who represents District No. 5.
(2) Two members appointed by the member of the governing authority of the city of
New Orleans who represents District A.
(3) One member appointed by the president of the governing authority of the city of
New Orleans.
Proposed law provides that members serve five-year staggered terms. Requires that
members serve without compensation, but authorizes reimbursement for expenses incurred
while attending to the business of the board or the district.
Proposed law provides for the powers and duties of the district, including but not limited to
the following:
(1) To sue and to be sued.
(2) To adopt, use, and alter at will a corporate seal.
(3) To adopt bylaws and rules and regulations.
